Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine), proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and mildly low blood glucose, suggesting possible diabetic nephropathy or another renal pathology. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) may indicate urinary tract involvement. No evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further assessment for underlying metabolic or renal disease.
